People anxiously try to anticipate the result by reading the expressions on the master counters' faces as they stream out onto the balcony to proclaim that YOU have won the election and are now the next King of the Beagus.

"Grass is not food, grass is what food eats" as the Beagus say. Every lifeform exists within a hierarchy of species with man at the top. They belive that eating lifeforms high up on the hierarchy is more beneficial to one's constitution. Eating another man would be the ultimate empowerment, but also an unthinkable crime as the legend of the brothers Sourà and Stigge tells them. Humans aside, they have a strong preference for meat and meat products.
